alpsPeerLocalIpAddr.name: alpsPeerLocalIpAddr
alpsPeerLocalIpAddr.description: The configured IP address used by the ALPS component in this router.

alpsPeerLocalAtpPort.name: alpsPeerLocalAtpPort
alpsPeerLocalAtpPort.description: The port number used locally by the ALPS peer at this router. This is a static value but the port number used can change in later versions. This is not a configured value but is embedded into the source code. This has been provided mainly to aid in debugging so that the operator knows which TCP port to look at. ATP is the ALPS Tunnelling Protocol, a Cisco proprietary way to tunnel ALPS data across a TCP link

alpsPeerKeepaliveTimeout.name: alpsPeerKeepaliveTimeout
alpsPeerKeepaliveTimeout.description: The TCP keep alive timeout value for Local ALPS Peer. Keepalives are sent out periodically at this interval to the remote peer.

alpsPeerKeepaliveMaxRetries.name: alpsPeerKeepaliveMaxRetries
alpsPeerKeepaliveMaxRetries.description: The number of keepalives sent with acknowledgement before declaring the remote peer dead. 0 implies that keepalives are turned off.

alpsPeerInCallsAcceptFlag.name: alpsPeerInCallsAcceptFlag
alpsPeerInCallsAcceptFlag.description: If this is true, calls are accepted from any peer. If this is false, calls are accepted only from those routers which have been explicitly configured using alps remote-peer commands.

alpsRemPeerTable.name: alpsRemPeerTable
alpsRemPeerTable.description: A list of Remote peers that the local ALPS peer can communicate with.

alpsRemPeerEntry.name: alpsRemPeerEntry
alpsRemPeerEntry.description: Each entry represents an Remote ALPS Peer.

alpsRemPeerIpAddr.name: alpsRemPeerIpAddr
alpsRemPeerIpAddr.description: The remote IP address for the TCP Connection.

alpsRemPeerConnType.name: alpsRemPeerConnType
alpsRemPeerConnType.description: Type of ALPS circuit established. Dynamic circuits are established only when there is data traffic that needs to be sent across and are closed when the alpsRemPeerIdleTimer expires. Permanent circuits stay up regardless of whether there is traffic across them or not.

alpsRemPeerLocalPort.name: alpsRemPeerLocalPort
alpsRemPeerLocalPort.description: The port number used locally by the tcp connection for the circuit. the initiator of a connection will dynamically assign a port number. the other end of the connection will have a well-known port number applicable to the encapsulation used by the connection - e.g. the value of alpsPeerLocalAtpPort for ATP connections.

alpsRemPeerRemotePort.name: alpsRemPeerRemotePort
alpsRemPeerRemotePort.description: The port number used by the remote end of the tcp connection for the circuit. the initiator of a connection will dynamically assign a port number. the other end of the connection will have a well-known port number applicable to the encapsulation used by the connection - e.g. the value of alpsPeerLocalAtpPort for ATP connections. If this connection was initiated by the local router, a port number will be dynamically selected. Otherwise the value of alpsPeerLocalAtpPort will be used (for ATP connections)

alpsRemPeerState.name: alpsRemPeerState
alpsRemPeerState.description: TCP Peer State. Initially the connection is in the closed state. For permanent connections, it starts opening the TCP connection immediately, but for dynamic ones, it waits till there is traffic addressed to the remote peer. It then progresses via opening into the opened state.

alpsRemPeerUptime.name: alpsRemPeerUptime
alpsRemPeerUptime.description: Time elapsed since TCP connection was established.

alpsRemPeerNumActiveCkts.name: alpsRemPeerNumActiveCkts
alpsRemPeerNumActiveCkts.description: Number of active ALPS circuits in this TCP session.

alpsRemPeerIdleTimer.name: alpsRemPeerIdleTimer
alpsRemPeerIdleTimer.description: The TCP session with the peer will be closed if there is no activity for alpsInactiveTimer seconds. This is valid only for dynamic circuits

alpsRemPeerAlarmsEnabled.name: alpsRemPeerAlarmsEnabled
alpsRemPeerAlarmsEnabled.description: Specifies whether alarms are generated for this remote Peer

alpsRemPeerTCPQlen.name: alpsRemPeerTCPQlen
alpsRemPeerTCPQlen.description: Maximum TCP Queue size allowed for this TCP session.

alpsRemPeerOutPackets.name: alpsRemPeerOutPackets
alpsRemPeerOutPackets.description: Number of packets transmitted to the remote peer.

alpsRemPeerOutOctets.name: alpsRemPeerOutOctets
alpsRemPeerOutOctets.description: Number of octets transmitted to the remote peer.

alpsRemPeerInPackets.name: alpsRemPeerInPackets
alpsRemPeerInPackets.description: Number of packets received from the remote peer.

alpsRemPeerInOctets.name: alpsRemPeerInOctets
alpsRemPeerInOctets.description: Number of octets received from the remote peer.

alpsRemPeerDropsGiant.name: alpsRemPeerDropsGiant
alpsRemPeerDropsGiant.description: Number of Packets dropped because they were larger than the maximum allowed packet size of 3840 bytes.

alpsRemPeerDropsQFull.name: alpsRemPeerDropsQFull
alpsRemPeerDropsQFull.description: Number of packets dropped because the TCP queue (of size alpsRemPeerTCPQlen) was full.

alpsRemPeerDropsPeerUnreach.name: alpsRemPeerDropsPeerUnreach
alpsRemPeerDropsPeerUnreach.description: Number of packets dropped because remote peer was unreachable.

alpsRemPeerRowStatus.name: alpsRemPeerRowStatus
alpsRemPeerRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table.

alpsRemPeerCfgTable.name: alpsRemPeerCfgTable
alpsRemPeerCfgTable.description: Table listing of all administered ALPS remote peer configuration entries on this node. Entries in this table can be created via a CLI command or via alpsRemPeerCfgRowStatus.

alpsRemPeerCfgEntry.name: alpsRemPeerCfgEntry
alpsRemPeerCfgEntry.description: Each entry represents an ALPS remote peer configuration entry on this node.

alpsRemPeerCfgIpAddr.name: alpsRemPeerCfgIpAddr
alpsRemPeerCfgIpAddr.description: The configured IP address of an ALPS remote peer.

alpsRemPeerCfgProtocol.name: alpsRemPeerCfgProtocol
alpsRemPeerCfgProtocol.description: The configured ALPS protocol encapsulation. This protocol encapsulation is at the layer above TCP.

alpsRemPeerCfgActivation.name: alpsRemPeerCfgActivation
alpsRemPeerCfgActivation.description: The configured type of ALPS peer activation.

alpsRemPeerCfgTCPQLen.name: alpsRemPeerCfgTCPQLen
alpsRemPeerCfgTCPQLen.description: The configured maximum TCP Queue size.

alpsRemPeerCfgIdleTimer.name: alpsRemPeerCfgIdleTimer
alpsRemPeerCfgIdleTimer.description: The configured idle timer for a dynamic activation peer.

alpsRemPeerCfgNoCircTimer.name: alpsRemPeerCfgNoCircTimer
alpsRemPeerCfgNoCircTimer.description: The configured no-circuit timer for a dynamic activation peer.

alpsRemPeerCfgAlarmsOn.name: alpsRemPeerCfgAlarmsOn
alpsRemPeerCfgAlarmsOn.description: The configured parameter which specifies whether alarms are generated for remote peer connections to the IP address in alpsRemPeerCfgIpAddr.

alpsRemPeerCfgStatRetry.name: alpsRemPeerCfgStatRetry
alpsRemPeerCfgStatRetry.description: The configured number of status retries.

alpsRemPeerCfgRowStatus.name: alpsRemPeerCfgRowStatus
alpsRemPeerCfgRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table.

alpsRemPeerConnTable.name: alpsRemPeerConnTable
alpsRemPeerConnTable.description: Table listing of all ALPS remote peer connections on this node.

alpsRemPeerConnEntry.name: alpsRemPeerConnEntry
alpsRemPeerConnEntry.description: Each entry represents an ALPS remote peer connection on this node.

alpsRemPeerConnIpAddr.name: alpsRemPeerConnIpAddr
alpsRemPeerConnIpAddr.description: The IP address of the ALPS remote peer.

alpsRemPeerConnIdString.name: alpsRemPeerConnIdString
alpsRemPeerConnIdString.description: A descriptive ASCII string that is used to distinguish among different peer connections to the same ALPS remote peer IP address.

alpsRemPeerConnLocalPort.name: alpsRemPeerConnLocalPort
alpsRemPeerConnLocalPort.description: The local TCP port number used by the underlying TCP connection to an ALPS remote peer.

alpsRemPeerConnForeignPort.name: alpsRemPeerConnForeignPort
alpsRemPeerConnForeignPort.description: The foreign (remote) TCP port number used by the underlying TCP connection to an ALPS remote peer.

alpsRemPeerConnState.name: alpsRemPeerConnState
alpsRemPeerConnState.description: The state of the connection to an ALPS remote peer.

alpsRemPeerConnProtocol.name: alpsRemPeerConnProtocol
alpsRemPeerConnProtocol.description: The ALPS protocol encapsulation used on the connection to the ALPS remote peer. This protocol encapsulation is a layer above TCP.

alpsRemPeerConnCreation.name: alpsRemPeerConnCreation
alpsRemPeerConnCreation.description: The stimulus for creating the peer connection object. The peer connection object may be created solely due to configuration (admin) or due to a combination of configuration and protocol events (learned).

alpsRemPeerConnActivation.name: alpsRemPeerConnActivation
alpsRemPeerConnActivation.description: Basis for activation a peer connection. A permanent activation peer connection will attempt to open immediately and stay open, regardless of the usage of the peer connection. A dynamic activation peer connection only opens when there is data to send and the peer connection will close if there are no data messages sent or received across the peer for the duration of the idle timer.

alpsRemPeerConnUptime.name: alpsRemPeerConnUptime
alpsRemPeerConnUptime.description: Elapsed time since the ALPS peer connection was successfully established.

alpsRemPeerConnNumActCirc.name: alpsRemPeerConnNumActCirc
alpsRemPeerConnNumActCirc.description: The number of ALPS virtual circuits using the connection to this ALPS remote peer.

alpsRemPeerConnLastTxRx.name: alpsRemPeerConnLastTxRx
alpsRemPeerConnLastTxRx.description: The value of sysUpTime when a peer data message was last transmitted or received across this ALPS remote peer connection. This timestamp is not update if the peer message is a peer status inquiry/response message.

alpsRemPeerConnLastRxAny.name: alpsRemPeerConnLastRxAny
alpsRemPeerConnLastRxAny.description: The value of sysUpTime when a peer data or status message is last received across the ALPS remote peer connection.

alpsRemPeerConnIdleTimer.name: alpsRemPeerConnIdleTimer
alpsRemPeerConnIdleTimer.description: A dynamic activation ALPS peer connection will be closed if zero peer data messages are sent or received for a length of time greater than or equal to this timer.

alpsRemPeerConnNoCircTimer.name: alpsRemPeerConnNoCircTimer
alpsRemPeerConnNoCircTimer.description: A dynamic activation ALPS peer connection will be closed if zero ALPS circuits are active or attempt to activate for a length of time greater than or equal to this timer.

alpsRemPeerConnTCPQLen.name: alpsRemPeerConnTCPQLen
alpsRemPeerConnTCPQLen.description: The maximum number of ALPS peer messages that can be queued in a single TCP session.

alpsRemPeerConnAlarmsOn.name: alpsRemPeerConnAlarmsOn
alpsRemPeerConnAlarmsOn.description: This parameter specifies whether ALPS alarms are generated for this ALPS remote peer connection.

alpsRemPeerConnStatIntvl.name: alpsRemPeerConnStatIntvl
alpsRemPeerConnStatIntvl.description: The time interval (in seconds) between transmission of consecutive ALPS Peer Status messages. These messages are only transmitted if zero messages are received on the peer connection for a length of time greater than or equal to this timer.

alpsRemPeerConnStatRetry.name: alpsRemPeerConnStatRetry
alpsRemPeerConnStatRetry.description: The number of consecutive unanswered ALPS Peer Status messages transmitted before closing the conenction to the ALPS remote peer.

alpsRemPeerConnDownReason.name: alpsRemPeerConnDownReason
alpsRemPeerConnDownReason.description: Reason that an ALPS Peer connection failed to open sauccessfully.

alpsRemPeerConnOutPackets.name: alpsRemPeerConnOutPackets
alpsRemPeerConnOutPackets.description: Number of packets transmitted on this ALPS remote peer connection.

alpsRemPeerConnOutOctets.name: alpsRemPeerConnOutOctets
alpsRemPeerConnOutOctets.description: Number of octets transmitted on this ALPS remote peer connection.

alpsRemPeerConnInPackets.name: alpsRemPeerConnInPackets
alpsRemPeerConnInPackets.description: Number of packets received on this ALPS remote peer connection.

alpsRemPeerConnInOctets.name: alpsRemPeerConnInOctets
alpsRemPeerConnInOctets.description: Number of octets received on this ALPS remote peer connection.

alpsRemPeerConnDropsGiant.name: alpsRemPeerConnDropsGiant
alpsRemPeerConnDropsGiant.description: Number of ALPS peer packets dropped due to exceeding the maximum allowed packet size of 3840 bytes.

alpsRemPeerConnDropsQFull.name: alpsRemPeerConnDropsQFull
alpsRemPeerConnDropsQFull.description: Number of ALPS peer packets dropped because the TCP output queue is full.

alpsRemPeerConnDropsUnreach.name: alpsRemPeerConnDropsUnreach
alpsRemPeerConnDropsUnreach.description: Number of ALPS peer packets dropped because the ALPS remote peer is unreachable.

alpsRemPeerConnDropsVersion.name: alpsRemPeerConnDropsVersion
alpsRemPeerConnDropsVersion.description: Number of ALPS peer packets dropped because of a version mismatch in the ALPS encapsulation.

alpsCktBaseTable.name: alpsCktBaseTable
alpsCktBaseTable.description: A list of ALPS circuits. This table contains variables common to central & remote routers.

alpsCktBaseName.name: alpsCktBaseName
alpsCktBaseName.description: Specifies the ALPS Circuit Name. This is unique within the network.

alpsCktBaseDlcType.name: alpsCktBaseDlcType
alpsCktBaseDlcType.description: Specifies what type of circuit this is. The X25 circuit is set up with the same name as the P1024 circuit so we need this variable to distinguish between the two, in case local switching is done.

alpsCktBasePriPeerAddr.name: alpsCktBasePriPeerAddr
alpsCktBasePriPeerAddr.description: This is the IP address of the Primary Central peer. It is mandatory to configure a primary peer, but the backup peer is optional.

alpsCktBaseAlarmsEnabled.name: alpsCktBaseAlarmsEnabled
alpsCktBaseAlarmsEnabled.description: Specifies whether alarms are generated for this ALPS circuit. Alarms can be syslog messages or SNMP traps - both are controlled using the same flags.

alpsCktBaseConnType.name: alpsCktBaseConnType
alpsCktBaseConnType.description: Specifies the ALPS Circuit Connection Type.

alpsCktBaseState.name: alpsCktBaseState
alpsCktBaseState.description: Indicates the state of ALPS Circuit.

alpsCktBaseNumActiveAscus.name: alpsCktBaseNumActiveAscus
alpsCktBaseNumActiveAscus.description: Reports the number of enabled ASCUs that are attached to this ALPS Circuit. Attachment of an ASCU to an ALPS circuit may occur due to configuration or due to information passed in a protocol message.

alpsCktBaseCurrentPeer.name: alpsCktBaseCurrentPeer
alpsCktBaseCurrentPeer.description: Reports the IP address of the peer that this ALPS circuit is currently connected to.

alpsCktBaseLifeTimeTimer.name: alpsCktBaseLifeTimeTimer
alpsCktBaseLifeTimeTimer.description: A data message that has been queued within the router for longer than this interval will be dropped.

alpsCktBaseHostLinkNumber.name: alpsCktBaseHostLinkNumber
alpsCktBaseHostLinkNumber.description: Specifies host link number (on Central router) for this ALPS Circuit. The host link number is used to provide a degree of transparency to the remote router. A single host link may correspond to multiple physical links between the central router and the host, which can then load-balance VCs across them.

alpsCktBaseHostLinkType.name: alpsCktBaseHostLinkType
alpsCktBaseHostLinkType.description: Specifies host link type(on Central router) for this ALPS Circuit.

alpsCktBaseRemHld.name: alpsCktBaseRemHld
alpsCktBaseRemHld.description: Specifies the HLD (High-level descriptor) of the AX.25/EMTOX host for this ALPS Circuit. This serves as an identifier for the host

alpsCktBaseLocalHld.name: alpsCktBaseLocalHld
alpsCktBaseLocalHld.description: Specifies the local HLD for this ALPS Circuit. HLDs are required at the host for both ends of the connection.

alpsCktBaseDownReason.name: alpsCktBaseDownReason
alpsCktBaseDownReason.description: Reports the reason why this ALPS Circuit is down, if it is down.

alpsCktBaseOutPackets.name: alpsCktBaseOutPackets
alpsCktBaseOutPackets.description: Number of packets transmitted to remote peer over this circuit.

alpsCktBaseOutOctets.name: alpsCktBaseOutOctets
alpsCktBaseOutOctets.description: Number of octets transmitted to remote peer over this circuit.

alpsCktBaseInPackets.name: alpsCktBaseInPackets
alpsCktBaseInPackets.description: Number of packets received from remote peer over this circuit.

alpsCktBaseInOctets.name: alpsCktBaseInOctets
alpsCktBaseInOctets.description: Number of octets received from remote peer over this circuit.

alpsCktBaseDropsCktDisabled.name: alpsCktBaseDropsCktDisabled
alpsCktBaseDropsCktDisabled.description: Number of packets dropped because the circuit was disabled. This would typically be packets that were queueued before the circuit was disabled which are now left in the queue.

alpsCktBaseDropsQOverflow.name: alpsCktBaseDropsQOverflow
alpsCktBaseDropsQOverflow.description: Number of packets dropped due to TCP Congestion.

alpsCktBaseDropsLifeTimeExpd.name: alpsCktBaseDropsLifeTimeExpd
alpsCktBaseDropsLifeTimeExpd.description: Number of packets which were queued within the router for longer than alpsCktBaseLifeTimeTimer.

alpsCktBaseEnabled.name: alpsCktBaseEnabled
alpsCktBaseEnabled.description: This specifies if the circuit has been enabled. After a circuit has been configured, it must be explicitly enabled in order for the circuit to be set up.

alpsCktBaseRowStatus.name: alpsCktBaseRowStatus
alpsCktBaseRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table.

alpsCktBaseCurrPeerConnId.name: alpsCktBaseCurrPeerConnId
alpsCktBaseCurrPeerConnId.description: A descriptive ASCII string that is used to distinguish among different peer connections to the same ALPS remote peer IP address.

alpsCktX25Table.name: alpsCktX25Table
alpsCktX25Table.description: A list of ALPS X.25 circuits. These entries exist only for X.25 circuits. hence this table would probably be empty at the remote router

alpsCktX25DlcType.name: alpsCktX25DlcType
alpsCktX25DlcType.description: Specifies what type of circuit this is.

alpsCktX25IfIndex.name: alpsCktX25IfIndex
alpsCktX25IfIndex.description: Reports the interface the circuit is on. This is the interface which is connected to the host

alpsCktX25LCN.name: alpsCktX25LCN
alpsCktX25LCN.description: The Logical Channel Number being used on the X.25 VC for this ALPS Circuit.

alpsCktX25HostX121.name: alpsCktX25HostX121
alpsCktX25HostX121.description: The X.121 address on the host side which the central router uses to connect to the host

alpsCktX25RemoteX121.name: alpsCktX25RemoteX121
alpsCktX25RemoteX121.description: X.121 address of the remote side. Remote here refers to the side that the ASCUS are connected to and is also referred to as the remote router.

alpsCktX25DropsVcReset.name: alpsCktX25DropsVcReset
alpsCktX25DropsVcReset.description: Number of packets dropped due to the VC being reset. These are packets that were queued up for transmission on that VC when it was reset

alpsCktP1024Table.name: alpsCktP1024Table
alpsCktP1024Table.description: A list of ALC or UTS Alps circuits.

alpsCktP1024DlcType.name: alpsCktP1024DlcType
alpsCktP1024DlcType.description: Specifies what type of circuit this is.

alpsCktP1024BackupPeerAddr.name: alpsCktP1024BackupPeerAddr
alpsCktP1024BackupPeerAddr.description: This is the IP address of the backup remote peer. This is optional and hence may not always exist.

alpsCktP1024RetryTimer.name: alpsCktP1024RetryTimer
alpsCktP1024RetryTimer.description: Specifies the interval at which a permanent ALPS circuit will attempt to reestablish the circuit in case it wasn't able to come up.

alpsCktP1024IdleTimer.name: alpsCktP1024IdleTimer
alpsCktP1024IdleTimer.description: If there is no traffic on a dynamic ALPS circuit for this interval, it will be cleared.

alpsCktP1024EmtoxX121.name: alpsCktP1024EmtoxX121
alpsCktP1024EmtoxX121.description: Specifies the X.121 address of the SVC established with EMTOX host. This field should be set to length zero in the case of PVCs (AX.25 host).

alpsCktP1024Ax25LCN.name: alpsCktP1024Ax25LCN
alpsCktP1024Ax25LCN.description: Specifies the Logical Channel Number being used on the PVC established with AX.25 host. This field should be set to zero in the case of SVCs (EMTOX host).

alpsCktP1024WinOut.name: alpsCktP1024WinOut
alpsCktP1024WinOut.description: Specifies X.25 transmit Window size on the Logical Channel Number of this ALPS Circuit.

alpsCktP1024WinIn.name: alpsCktP1024WinIn
alpsCktP1024WinIn.description: Specifies the X.25 receive Window size on the Logical Channel Number of this ALPS Circuit.

alpsCktP1024OutPktSize.name: alpsCktP1024OutPktSize
alpsCktP1024OutPktSize.description: Specifies the X.25 maxiumum output Packet size on the Logical Channel Number of this ALPS Circuit. The default output Packet size for AX.25 is 240 bytes and 128 bytes for EMTOX.

alpsCktP1024InPktSize.name: alpsCktP1024InPktSize
alpsCktP1024InPktSize.description: Specifies X.25 maximum input Packet size on the Logical Channel Number of this ALPS Circuit. The default input Packet size for AX.25 is 240 bytes and 128 bytes for EMTOX.

alpsCktP1024SvcMsgList.name: alpsCktP1024SvcMsgList
alpsCktP1024SvcMsgList.description: Specifies the Service Message List Number to use on this ALPS Circuit. This allows custom service messages to be sent for ASCUs on a particular circuit. Service messages are sent out by the router to the ASCU when abnormal conditions occur, and are displayed on the terminal. There is a default set of service messages, usually referred to as List 0. However, it is possible to configure custom sets of service messages for display, selectable on a per-circuit basis.

alpsCktP1024SvcMsgIntvl.name: alpsCktP1024SvcMsgIntvl
alpsCktP1024SvcMsgIntvl.description: Specifies Service Message Time Interval for the Service messages to be sent this ALPS Circuit. This controls how frequently the messages are repeated when an error condition (e.g. network being down) persists.

alpsCktP1024DropsUnkAscu.name: alpsCktP1024DropsUnkAscu
alpsCktP1024DropsUnkAscu.description: Number of packets that were found to be from an Unknown ASCU (i.e. an ASCU that had not been configured) and hence were dropped.

alpsCktP1024RowStatus.name: alpsCktP1024RowStatus
alpsCktP1024RowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table.

alpsCktP1024MatipCloseDelay.name: alpsCktP1024MatipCloseDelay
alpsCktP1024MatipCloseDelay.description: Specifies the minumum delay between transmission of a MATIP Close and the transmission of a MATIP Session Open for this ALPS circuit.

alpsCktAscuTable.name: alpsCktAscuTable
alpsCktAscuTable.description: A list of ASCUs for each ALPS Circuit. This may not include all ASCUs which have this circuit configured as alpsAscuCktName because some ASCUs may be rejected by the host while setting up the circuit.

alpsCktAscuEntry.name: alpsCktAscuEntry
alpsCktAscuEntry.description: Details of ASCUs on ASCU Circuits.

alpsCktAscuCktName.name: alpsCktAscuCktName
alpsCktAscuCktName.description: The name of the ALPS circuit which this ASCU is on. The circuit may be always up (for permanent circuits) or get set up (dynamic circuits) when there is traffic on one of the ASCUs which are set up for that circuit.

alpsCktAscuCktDlcType.name: alpsCktAscuCktDlcType
alpsCktAscuCktDlcType.description: Specifies what type of circuit this is. The X.25 circuit is set up with the same name as the ALC circuit so we need this variable to distinguish between the two.

alpsCktAscuA1.name: alpsCktAscuA1
alpsCktAscuA1.description: A1 value. This is used along with the alpsCktAscuA2 value to identify the ASCU within the circuit.

alpsCktAscuA2.name: alpsCktAscuA2
alpsCktAscuA2.description: A2 value. This is used along with the alpsCktAscuA1 value to identify the ASCU within the circuit.

alpsCktAscuIfIndex.name: alpsCktAscuIfIndex
alpsCktAscuIfIndex.description: Reports the interface the ASCU is on. This field, along with alpsCktAscuId is provided so that it is possible to correlate this information with the configured ASCU information in alpsAscuTable

alpsCktAscuId.name: alpsCktAscuId
alpsCktAscuId.description: Reports the ASCU Identifier which uniquely identifies an ASCU on a given interface. This value is the Interface Address (IA) for ALC and the Remote Identifier (RID) for UTS. A value of 0 indicates that the ASCU id is either unavailable or not applicable.

alpsCktAscuStatus.name: alpsCktAscuStatus
alpsCktAscuStatus.description: Reports the ASCU status - ASCUs configured on the circuit can be rejected at the host and would then be marked REJECT. Also, ASCUs configured after the circuit has been established are not added dynamically to the circuit but are marked NEW and get added when the circuit gets established the next time. ASCUs waiting for an accept or reject response from the host are marked as PENDING. ASCUs that were accepted by the host are marked OK.

alpsIfP1024Table.name: alpsIfP1024Table
alpsIfP1024Table.description: A list of interfaces running the P1024B or P1024C protocols

alpsIfP1024EncapType.name: alpsIfP1024EncapType
alpsIfP1024EncapType.description: Reports the encapsulation type for this Serial Interface.

alpsIfP1024PollRespTimeout.name: alpsIfP1024PollRespTimeout
alpsIfP1024PollRespTimeout.description: Specifies the Poll Response Time out value.

alpsIfP1024GATimeout.name: alpsIfP1024GATimeout
alpsIfP1024GATimeout.description: Specifies the time-out delay between receipt of first character of an input sequence solicited by a poll and receipt of GA sequence.

alpsIfP1024PollPauseTimeout.name: alpsIfP1024PollPauseTimeout
alpsIfP1024PollPauseTimeout.description: Specifies the minimum delay between two poll cycles. Thus the poll pause interval is counted from the instant when the first ASCU in the poll list is polled. Note that this is the delay between two traversals of the entire poll list rather than the interval between two consecutive polls. The actual delay will probably be more than the value of this variable.

alpsIfP1024MaxErrCnt.name: alpsIfP1024MaxErrCnt
alpsIfP1024MaxErrCnt.description: Specifies a maximum error count for this interface. After an ASCU link comes up, if it experiences this number of errors the ASCU link will be shutdown. The default value of 0 results in the ASCU link never being shutdown.

alpsIfP1024MaxRetrans.name: alpsIfP1024MaxRetrans
alpsIfP1024MaxRetrans.description: Specifies the maximum number of times an output message will be retransmitted before it is discarded. This is relevant only for P1024C (UTS). For ALC, a value of 0 will be returned. Note that legal values for UTS are 1-10

alpsIfP1024CurrErrCnt.name: alpsIfP1024CurrErrCnt
alpsIfP1024CurrErrCnt.description: Reports the number of errors currently existing for this ASCU link. When this equals alpsIfP1024MaxErrCnt then the ASCU link will be shut down, unless alpsIfP1024MaxErrCnt equals 0 in which case the ascu link is never shut down due to error thresholds being exceeded

alpsIfP1024MinGoodPollResp.name: alpsIfP1024MinGoodPollResp
alpsIfP1024MinGoodPollResp.description: Specifies the number of good Poll Responses to be received from an ASCU before it can be declared up.

alpsIfP1024PollingRatio.name: alpsIfP1024PollingRatio
alpsIfP1024PollingRatio.description: Specifies how many times ASCUs in UP state are polled before an ASCU in DOWN state is polled again.

alpsIfP1024NumAscus.name: alpsIfP1024NumAscus
alpsIfP1024NumAscus.description: Reports the number of ASCUs configured on this Serial Port.

alpsIfP1024ServMsgFormat.name: alpsIfP1024ServMsgFormat
alpsIfP1024ServMsgFormat.description: Specifies the format of the service message sent to an ASCU on this interface.

alpsIfP1024ServMsgStatusChange.name: alpsIfP1024ServMsgStatusChange
alpsIfP1024ServMsgStatusChange.description: Specifies whether service messages generated due to an ALPS circuit status change or an ASCU status change, will be forwarded to the ASCU.

alpsIfP1024ServMsgDropTermAddr.name: alpsIfP1024ServMsgDropTermAddr
alpsIfP1024ServMsgDropTermAddr.description: Specifies whether the service message will be sent to the same terminal address of the dropped message or the configured value.

alpsIfHLinkTable.name: alpsIfHLinkTable
alpsIfHLinkTable.description: A list of interfaces running AX.25/EMTOX host link protocols. These are on the central router

alpsIfHLinkEntry.name: alpsIfHLinkEntry
alpsIfHLinkEntry.description: Details of AX.25/EMTOX host link protocols on an Interface.

alpsIfHLinkHostHld.name: alpsIfHLinkHostHld
alpsIfHLinkHostHld.description: Specifies the HLD of the AX.25/EMTOX host connected on this Interface. The HLD(High-level descriptor) serves as an identifier along with the hostlink number and helps correlate the ALPS circuit to a host link. The hex range is 0x1 to 0xFFFF which corresponds to 1 ... 65535 in decimal.

alpsIfHLinkNumber.name: alpsIfHLinkNumber
alpsIfHLinkNumber.description: Specifies the configured Host Link Number on this Serial Interface.

alpsIfHLinkX25ProtocolType.name: alpsIfHLinkX25ProtocolType
alpsIfHLinkX25ProtocolType.description: Reports the encapsulation type for this Serial Interface - AX.25 or EMTOX.

alpsIfHLinkAx25PvcDamp.name: alpsIfHLinkAx25PvcDamp
alpsIfHLinkAx25PvcDamp.description: The purpose of this object is to handle the link-damping for an AX.25 host. If the PVC goes inactive (i.e. link goes down, etc...) for PVCDampValue seconds, then PVC will be destroyed as well as the associated ALPS circuit.

alpsIfHLinkEmtoxHostX121.name: alpsIfHLinkEmtoxHostX121
alpsIfHLinkEmtoxHostX121.description: Specfies the X.121 address of this EMTOX host.

alpsIfHLinkActiveCkts.name: alpsIfHLinkActiveCkts
alpsIfHLinkActiveCkts.description: Reports the number of ALPS Ckts established with this host.

alpsAscuTable.name: alpsAscuTable
alpsAscuTable.description: A list of ALPS ASCUs on an interface. This is defined only at the remote router.

alpsAscuId.name: alpsAscuId
alpsAscuId.description: Specifies the ASCU Identifier and uniquely identifies an ASCU on a given interface. This value is the Interface Address (IA) for ALC and the Remote Identifier (RID) for UTS. This uniquely identifies an ASCU on a given interface.

alpsAscuCktName.name: alpsAscuCktName
alpsAscuCktName.description: Specifies the ALPS Circuit Name for the circuit that is to be used for this ASCU's data. Note that all ASCUs on a physical interface may not use the same ALPS circuit to connect to the central router

alpsAscuAlarmsEnabled.name: alpsAscuAlarmsEnabled
alpsAscuAlarmsEnabled.description: Specifies whether alarms (syslog messages or SNMP traps) will be generated for this ASCU.

alpsAscuRetryOption.name: alpsAscuRetryOption
alpsAscuRetryOption.description: Specifies the retry option for this ASCU. This specifies the error message to be sent to the terminal when a message is dropped at the router. The terminal has three choices - either retransmit the last message (if the terminal can buffer it), re-enter the last message sent or do nothing. Based on the terminal's capabilities, one of these three is configured for the ASCU. Note that this option is the same for all terminals connected to an ASCU because the ALPS feature does not handle individual terminals

alpsAscuMaxMsgLength.name: alpsAscuMaxMsgLength
alpsAscuMaxMsgLength.description: Specifies Maximum length of Input Message that can be received from this ASCU.

alpsAscuFwdStatusOption.name: alpsAscuFwdStatusOption
alpsAscuFwdStatusOption.description: If this flag is set, status messages received from the ASCU are forwarded to the host. Otherwise they are discarded. Note that these are relevant only for P1024C (UTS). For ALC, a value of FALSE will be returned.

alpsAscuState.name: alpsAscuState
alpsAscuState.description: Reports the current ASCU Status. ASCUs are initially in disabled state. They are enabled from the parser if the operator wants to. This takes them to an UP state from which they go to a DOWN state if there are too many errors.

alpsAscuDownReason.name: alpsAscuDownReason
alpsAscuDownReason.description: Reports the Down reason for this ASCU if it is down.

alpsAscuOutPackets.name: alpsAscuOutPackets
alpsAscuOutPackets.description: Number of packets transmitted to this ASCU.

alpsAscuOutOctets.name: alpsAscuOutOctets
alpsAscuOutOctets.description: Number of octets transmitted to this ASCU.

alpsAscuInPackets.name: alpsAscuInPackets
alpsAscuInPackets.description: Number of packets received from this ASCU

alpsAscuInOctets.name: alpsAscuInOctets
alpsAscuInOctets.description: Number of octets received from this ASCU.

alpsAscuDropsGarbledPkts.name: alpsAscuDropsGarbledPkts
alpsAscuDropsGarbledPkts.description: The number of packets dropped due to the inability to properly decode them. Examples of garbled packets include packets with bad CRCs or bad header information

alpsAscuDropsAscuDown.name: alpsAscuDropsAscuDown
alpsAscuDropsAscuDown.description: The number of packets dropped because the ASCU had previously been declared DOWN due to error thresholds being exceeded.

alpsAscuDropsAscuDisabled.name: alpsAscuDropsAscuDisabled
alpsAscuDropsAscuDisabled.description: The number of packets dropped because the ASCU had previously been declared to be in disabled state.

alpsAscuEnabled.name: alpsAscuEnabled
alpsAscuEnabled.description: Specifies whether the ASCU has been enabled or not. After the ASCU has been configured, it must be explicitly enabled to allow it to be polled.

alpsAscuRowStatus.name: alpsAscuRowStatus
alpsAscuRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table.

alpsAscuAutoReset.name: alpsAscuAutoReset
alpsAscuAutoReset.description: Specifies whether a reset command will be automatically issued to any non-responsive ALC ASCUs.

alpsSvcMsgTable.name: alpsSvcMsgTable
alpsSvcMsgTable.description: A list of service messages and its associated number. There is a default list of service messages (list 0) as well as user-configurable service messages. On a per-circuit basis, the service message list to use can be selected. The user-configured service message lists are defined in this table. Note that the default service messages are not part of this table.

alpsSvcMsgEntry.name: alpsSvcMsgEntry
alpsSvcMsgEntry.description: Service Messages configured along with its List number and Service Message Number in that list.

alpsSvcMsgListNum.name: alpsSvcMsgListNum
alpsSvcMsgListNum.description: Specifies the Service Msg Number of this Service Msg. A maximum of 8 Service Message lists can be configured not including the one for Default/System (when alpsSvcMsgListNum = 0) Service messages.

alpsSvcMsgNum.name: alpsSvcMsgNum
alpsSvcMsgNum.description: Specifies the Service Msg Number of this Service Msg. A Maximum of 8 messages can be present.

alpsSvcMsgRowStatus.name: alpsSvcMsgRowStatus
alpsSvcMsgRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table.

alpsX121ToIpTransTable.name: alpsX121ToIpTransTable
alpsX121ToIpTransTable.description: A Translation table between X.121 address and IP address. This is intended to allow a connection to be established to the appropriate remote router. The X121 address in the call packet is used to look up the IP address of the remote peer

alpsX121ToIpTransEntry.name: alpsX121ToIpTransEntry
alpsX121ToIpTransEntry.description: A mapping table between X.121 address and IP address.

alpsX121.name: alpsX121
alpsX121.description: Specfies the X.121 address of the VC established with EMTOX host.

alpsIpAddress.name: alpsIpAddress
alpsIpAddress.description: This is the IP address of the remote peer which maps onto the X.121 address.

alpsX121ToIpTransRowStatus.name: alpsX121ToIpTransRowStatus
alpsX121ToIpTransRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table.

alpsPeerStatusChange.name: alpsPeerStatusChange
alpsPeerStatusChange.description: This Notification is generated when there is a change in state for the peer connection, provided alarms are enabled for that peer.

alpsCktStatusChange.name: alpsCktStatusChange
alpsCktStatusChange.description: This Notification has to be generated whenever there is a state change for the ALPS circuit, provided alarms are enabled for that circuit

alpsAscuStatusChange.name: alpsAscuStatusChange
alpsAscuStatusChange.description: This Notification has to be generated whenever there is a change in ASCU status, provided alarms are enabled for that ASCU

alpsPeerConnStatusChange.name: alpsPeerConnStatusChange
alpsPeerConnStatusChange.description: This Notification is generated when there is a change in state for an ALPS peer connection, provided alarms are enabled for that peer connection.

alpsCktOpenFailure.name: alpsCktOpenFailure
alpsCktOpenFailure.description: This Notification is generated whenever there is an open failure for the ALPS circuit, provided alarms are enabled for that circuit

alpsCktPartialReject.name: alpsCktPartialReject
alpsCktPartialReject.description: This Notification is generated whenever there is an open confirmation that contains a list of rejected ASCUs for the ALPS circuit, provided alarms are enabled for that circuit
